ness. Our objective is sustainable growth, currency stability, and mass job creation.",icon:(0,r.jsx)(d.Currency,{size:28})},{title:"National Security and Stability",description:"Security is the foundation of society's development. We will strengthen intelligence coordination, modernise law enforcement, improve border security, enhance military welfare, and promote community partnership frameworks to prevent crime and insurgency. Security policy must be professional, not politicised.",icon:(0,r.jsx)(c.Security,{size:28})},{title:"Youth Development and Innovation",description:"Over 60 percent of Nigeria's population is under 35. This demographic must become our greatest advantage. We will reform the educational curricula, expand vocational and technical education, invest in digital infrastructure, and create structured entrepreneurship financing programmes. Youth must move from survival to innovation.",icon:(0,r.jsx)(u.Idea,{size:28})},{title:"Healthcare and Social Protection",description:"Primary healthcare must be revitalised. Funding must be transparent and efficiently managed. We will strengthen universal health coverage, health insurance, support public private partnerships in health infrastructure, and implement targeted social safety programmes for vulnerable citizens. Healthcare access should not depend on income level.",icon:(0,r.jsx)(p.HealthCross,{size:28})},{title:"Education Reform",description:"Education is national security. We will modernise curricula, strengthen teacher training institutions, integrate digital literacy at all levels, and improve research funding in universities and polytechnics. Our goal is to produce globally competitive graduates prepared for a modern economy.",icon:(0,r.jsx)(h.Education,{size:28})},{title:"Governance and Institutional Reform",description:"Strong institutions ensure national stability beyond individuals. NDC will digitise government processes, enforce procurement transparency, protect whistleblowers, strengthen anti